"a.弱小的，发育不良的 【英】 adj.弱小的，发育不 良的(slight or inferior in power; weak) 【考】 measly : contemptibly / puny : weakly(卑鄙的对应下贱的/ 弱小的对应虚弱的) 【记】 可能是pony(小马)的 变体 【例】 puny little arms and legs adj. 体格弱小的; 微不足道的 【记】源于: pony(小马)pu扑, ny你: 我敢扑上去打你, 是因为你体格弱小的 【类】measly: contemptibly = puny: weakly卑鄙的就是下贱的 = 弱小的就是虚弱的 【参】enormous(adj 巨大的) 【记】pony 小马是弱小的；音：怕你，我怕了你了，你这么强，我这么弱 puny (adj.)  1570s, ""inferior in rank"" (1540s as a noun, ""junior pupil, freshman""), from Middle French puisné (Modern French puîné), from Old French puisne ""born later, younger, youngest"" (12c., contrasted with aisné ""first-born""), from puis nez, from puis ""afterward"" (from Vulgar Latin *postius, from Latin postea ""after this, hereafter,"" from post ""after,"" see post-, + ea ""there"") + Old French né ""born,"" from Latin natus, past participle of nasci ""be born"" (Old Latin gnasci; see genus). Sense of ""small, weak, insignificant"" first recorded 1590s. Compare puisne. Related: Puniness."
